record_data.record_title: IND/COMM END-USER ELECTRIC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
record_data.record_plain_text: PILOT POWER GROUP, INC. (PPG) IND/COMM END-USER ELECTRIC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 1. Availability: An eligible commercial/industrial end-user (End-User) of electricity entering into an agreement with Pilot Power Group, Inc. (PPG) may make electric energy or energy and capacity that it has purchased from a generator, supplier or marketer available under this rate schedule to PPG for resale on its behalf at market-based rates. PPG makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale. 2. Applicability: This Rate Schedule permits PPG to resell electric energy and/or capacity on behalf of End-Users and applies to all sales of energy or capacity conducted or administered by PPG on behalf of End-Users, not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of PPG. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established between the purchaser and PPG. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and PPG. 5. Affiliate Sales Prohibited. No sale may be made pursuant to this Rate Schedule to any public utility with a franchised electric service territory that is controlled by, or under common control with, or controlling PPG. 6. Effective Date. This Rate Schedule shall be effective on September 18, 2007. 7. Compliance with Commission Regulations: PPG shall comply with the provision of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning sellers market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the sellers market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning sellers market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 8. Limitation and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. The following are waivers of the Commissions Regulation were granted pursuant to a FERC Letter Order dated April 30, 2001 in Docket No. ER01-1699-000, as revised in FERC Letter Order dated July 5, 2007: (1) Subparts B and C of Part 35, regarding the filing of rate schedules, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 (which requires applicant to file a Notice of Cancellation or Termination when it ceases its marketing activities), and 35.16 (which requires applicant to file a notice of succession whenever its name or operational control is changed). (2) Part 41, regarding accounts, records, and memoranda on behalf of PPG and its end-users; (3) Part 101, regarding the uniform system of accounts on behalf of PPG and its end-users; and; (4) Part 141, regarding statements and reports on behalf of PPG and its end-users. 9. Seller Category: PPG is a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
